                              <img src="/sites/worldliteraturetoday.org/files/Lahiri-b.jpg" alt="" width="" height=""  border="1" />
                                                              <br/> 
                                <div class="phototagleft">
                                  
                                </div>
                                                          </div>
                                                                                            <p class="word-copy-lh-mb" style="line-height:normal;"><a href="https://hcommons.org/members/hlahiri/"><strong>Hiranmoy Lahiri</strong></a><strong> </strong>is an emerging Kolkata-based translator, book reviewer, and freelance writer with a master’s degree in English. His latest work, <em>Kaleidoscope of Life: Selected Short Stories</em>, a translation of sixteen stories by Bibhutibhushan Bandyopadhyay, was published by Hawakal in 2024. His translations have appeared in <em>Muse India Literary Journal</em> and the <em>Bombay Literary Magazine</em>. One of his translations was longlisted for the 2024 Mozhi Translation Prize. Lahiri has also contributed articles to various national and international publications, including <em>The Statesman</em>, <em>Women Exclusive</em>, <em>Flickside</em>, <em>Offscreen</em>, <em>Asian Movie Pulse</em>, <em>Asia-Pacific Journal: Japan Focus</em>, and <em>Asiatic: IIUM Journal of English Language and Literature</em>.</p>
